techmeme.title: Stability AI announces Stable Fast 3D, a generative AI model for rapid 3D asset generation, says it can generate a 3D asset from a single image in 0.5 seconds (Sean Michael Kerner/VentureBeat)
Zomato's stock rose as much as 19% on August 2 after it reported Q1 profits up 125x to $30.2M, vs. ~$238K a year ago; Zomato's shares gained 110% in 2024 (Hritam Mukherjee/Reuters)
A Holdings Corp., a holding company owned equally by SoftBank and Naver, plans to sell down its stake in LY's ~$1B tender; LY operates Line messaging app (Mayumi Negishi/Bloomberg)
Nintendo reports Q1 revenue down 46.5% YoY to ~$1.65B, vs. ~$1.92B exp., net profit down 55.3% YoY to ~$536M, and Switch sales down 46% YoY to 2.1M units (Arjun Kharpal/CNBC)
Study: a year after Meta blocked news content in Canada due to the Online News Act, Canadians' total engagement with news content on social media is down 43% (The Canadian Press)
